hold on; till at last—owing to the perpendicular strain from the lead-lined 
chocks of the boats, whence the three ropes went straight down into the 
blue—the gunwales of the bows were almost even with the water, while the 
three sterns tilted high in the air. And the whale soon ceasing to sound, for 
some time they remained in that attitude, fearful of expending more line, 
